INSERT INTO `rule` VALUES (558,8,'LUP.6.3','1. Any point inside NMOS source/drain {{{N+ ACTIVE INTERACT CPODE {206;32}} INTERACT TrGATE} NOT PO} SPACE to nearest LUP PWSTRAP in same PW. {Figure XXX} 2. Any point inside PMOS source/drain {{{P+ ACTIVE INTERACT CPODE {206;32}} INTERACT TrGATE} NOT PO} SPACE to nearest LUP NWSTRAP in same NW. {Figure XXX} The LUP PW {NW} STRAP to N+ {P+} ACTIVE space requirement is dependent on ''LUP STRAP group size'' , ''NW strait width'' and application spec. a. The LUP NW {PW} STRAP group means LUP STRAPs with space <= 0.6 um along same NW {PW} strait. DRC counts total fin number in same LUP STRAP group. Total fin number each of LUP STRAP = {{{LUP STRAP vertical width - 0.008} / 0.030 + 1} * {POLY count -1}} . b. For NW strait width judgment , it takes minimum width of NW. DRC considers NW strait width from where STRAP located to where N/PMOS placed. c. There are 2 DRC options , i.e. LUP_VTRIG_25C_1d60V and LUP_VTRIG_25C_1d55V , to control rule spec by application. By default , both options are turned on. For details  , please refer toTable Exception: ACTIVE OD not connect to VC or MP	<=	Table XXX ','New','','hyyua',1,'hyyua',1,'',0,'',0,'','2019-05-03 08:19:29',0,NULL,NULL);
